Reasoning: The paper deals with communication in fast fading channels with channel state information, which falls under the domain of information theory and communication. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the dispersion of the channel, which is a measure of the channel's variability, and its connection to the error exponent, which falls under the domain of statistical inference and signal processing. Therefore, cs.SI (Signal Processing), cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), and cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) are also likely sub-categories.
